  "turns": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "Okay so — *[exhales dramatically]* — I just got out of another relationship where I was, like, the one doing everything. Trying, planning, initiating, *caring*... and he's already posting vacation photos with someone new, looking completely unbothered. So. What is wrong with me, and how do I stop picking these people?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What makes you so sure something is wrong with *you*?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I mean — *[laughs a little]* — because it's happened three times? Like, at some point the common denominator is me, right? I'm not an idiot. I can see the pattern. I just... I keep ending up in the same configuration where I'm the one leaning in and they're the one just... *existing*, you know? Barely showing up. And I'm over here orchestrating the whole relationship like some kind of — I don't know — anxious event planner."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "I love that image — anxious event planner. What does she get out of planning everything?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*[slight pause, then a little smile]*\n\nShe gets... I mean, she gets to feel needed? She's useful. She's the one holding it together, so there's always something to do. There's always a next move to make.\n\n*[beat]*\n\nWhich, okay, I can hear how that sounds. But I want to be clear — I wasn't doing it because I *liked* it. I was doing it because if I didn't, nothing would happen. He genuinely would not have initiated a single date in the last six months if I hadn't. That's not me being anxious, that's just... accurate."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "Both things can be true — he really wasn't showing up, *and* something in you finds a kind of safety in being the one who never has to wait and find out.\n\nWhat happens if you don't make the next move?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*[rolls eyes slightly]*\n\nI mean... nothing happens. That's the point. That's what I'm saying. It's not like I was choosing to be the planner, it's that the alternative was just — silence. Absence. So what was I supposed to do, just sit there?\n\n*[fidgets a little]*\n\nAnd I've tried that, by the way. The whole \"pull back and see if he reaches out\" thing. And sometimes he does, eventually, after like four days, and it feels... I don't know. It feels like a relief but also kind of hollow? Like, okay, you texted, congratulations.\n\n*[waves hand dismissively]*\n\nBut that's about him being avoidant, not about me needing to be in control or whatever you're implying."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "I'm not trying to catch you in something. I'm just curious about that word — hollow. What's actually happening for you in that moment when he finally texts?"
    }
  ],
